# compare worked example 1: output 1 if input < 0.5, else 0. Only ifless is
# patched; ifequal/ifgreater/else are omitted so those relations fall back to
# else's default (0). (else IS effectively present via default here because one
# of the four -- ifless -- is patched, so the all-omitted->ifequal=1 rule does
# NOT apply; equal falls back to else=0.)
patch <<<
[compare]
    input   = I1
    compare = 0.5
    ifless  = 1
    output  = O1
>>>
@0 set I1 0.3
@0 expect O1 1
@1 set I1 0.7
@1 expect O1 0
@2 set I1 0.5
@2 expect O1 0
